    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 311.122 R61/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have already had the honor to
                        acknowledge<note n="1" xml:id="d458fn1">Not printed.</note> your
                    excellency’s note of the 11th [etc.]. I now have the honor to present through
                    your excellency the thanks of President Díaz to President Taft for his promise
                    thoroughly to investigate the incident of the burning at the stake of the
                    Mexican Antonio Rodríguez, in Texas.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. L. De la Barra.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
